<p>The <code>trim</code> function removes whitespace from both ends of a string.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}$sampleText | trim{close}</pre>
<p>Original: "<b>{$sampleText}</b>"</p>
<p>Trimmed: "<b>{$sampleText | trim}</b>"</p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}'  HELLO WORLD  ' | trim | lower | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Clean and format: <b>{'  HELLO WORLD  ' | trim | lower | capitalize}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'   john.doe@example.com   ' | trim | before('@') | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Username from padded email: <b>{'   john.doe@example.com   ' | trim | before('@') | upper}</b></p>

<h2>Form Input Cleaning</h2>
<pre>{open}'  user input  ' | trim | lower | replace(' ', '_'){close}</pre>
<p>Sanitized input: <b>{'  user input  ' | trim | lower | replace(' ', '_')}</b></p>

<h2>Complex Chain</h2>
<pre>{open}'   /path/to/file.txt   ' | trim | afterLast('/') | beforeLast('.') | upper{close}</pre>
<p>Filename from padded path: <b>{'   /path/to/file.txt   ' | trim | afterLast('/') | beforeLast('.') | upper}</b></p>
